31:30.758 --> 31:33.965
and then complain
when he steals your car.

31:35.517 --> 31:36.896
Let's be clear.

31:37.068 --> 31:40.586
A swat on the butt with a hand,
that's a spanking,

31:40.724 --> 31:44.931
but what Donielle Lyons did
was beat his backside repeatedly

31:45.068 --> 31:48.758
with a leather belt.
He cried for her to stop.

31:49.620 --> 31:53.379
She left raised welts
on his skin. He's nine.

31:53.689 --> 31:57.862
Donielle inflicted bodily injury
on a child.

31:58.344 --> 31:59.896
She hit him so hard

32:00.034 --> 32:03.068
that when he tried to run away,
he fell and broke his arm.

32:04.586 --> 32:06.310
Now, the defense
would have you think

32:06.448 --> 32:10.172
that this is routine discipline
to thwart future infractions.

32:11.172 --> 32:16.172
I want you to see it
for what it is: child abuse.

32:17.793 --> 32:20.931
And you need to hold Donielle
accountable for that.

32:42.344 --> 32:44.103
Why the long face, Bambi?
I heard you went

32:44.241 --> 32:47.310
all the way into the jail
to find your lost client.

32:47.448 --> 32:50.034
He was in jail for two days
for a dog walking ticket,

32:50.172 --> 32:51.586
I mean, how does
that even happen?

32:51.724 --> 32:53.344
Oh come on, your cherry
must be popped by now.

32:53.482 --> 32:56.034
Why don't you quit acting
like a virgin in a whore house.

32:56.448 --> 32:58.206
Why are you so mean?

32:59.482 --> 33:01.551
Go grab us a couple
more martinis.

33:01.965 --> 33:03.655
You know I don't work
for you, right?

33:06.448 --> 33:09.310
Judge Sullivan.
Congratulations.

33:09.517 --> 33:14.689
Well, thank you. Have you, um...
Have you seen my Gwen?

33:17.965 --> 33:19.482
She's not coming, is she?

33:20.344 --> 33:23.137
You know she avoids me
when she's angry at me

33:23.689 --> 33:26.103
or when she's behind
in her bills.

33:27.034 --> 33:30.655
So, how are you girls doing
with your bills?

33:31.655 --> 33:33.862
Good, good.

33:35.793 --> 33:37.000
Mm-hmm.

33:45.413 --> 33:49.344
- You don't know who I am.
- Should I?

33:49.931 --> 33:51.965
I'm Audrey Dotson.

33:52.517 --> 33:56.068
Oh. Judge Dotson's wife.
Pleasure.

34:00.137 --> 34:04.344
- You're not the first you know.
- Beg your pardon?

34:04.827 --> 34:06.551
I know you're sleeping
with my husband.

34:06.689 --> 34:08.862
- I'm sorry, I--
- Don't bother.

34:09.310 --> 34:11.655
You're not the first
and you won't be the last,

34:11.793 --> 34:15.206
so you go have your fun,
but know this.

34:15.586 --> 34:17.586
He always comes home.

34:19.758 --> 34:23.379
And frankly, he's done better.

34:44.413 --> 34:46.758
In the matter of the People
versus Donielle Lyons,

34:46.896 --> 34:49.103
on the charge of assault
in the second degree,

34:49.482 --> 34:51.344
we the jury find
the defendant...

34:51.586 --> 34:52.965
guilty.

34:58.862 --> 35:01.344
Donielle, we are so sorry.

35:04.896 --> 35:07.586
Thank you. Thank you.

35:20.620 --> 35:22.551
I have my quarrels
with hitting your kid,

35:22.689 --> 35:25.068
but 18 months of state
and losing custody.

35:25.206 --> 35:28.068
As if he's better off
without his mother.

35:28.241 --> 35:29.689
Jesus.

35:31.241 --> 35:33.965
Let me see if I understand.
You recuse Blackburn,

35:34.103 --> 35:36.862
even though I explicitly
told you not to and you lost?

35:37.275 --> 35:38.931
Take your vacation days,
all of them.

35:39.137 --> 35:41.068
But Tom, she was not going
to give us--

35:41.379 --> 35:43.551
Every part of me wants
to suspend you right now,

35:43.689 --> 35:45.517
so don't push it.
I don't want to see your face

35:45.655 --> 35:47.034
until those days
have zeroed out.

35:47.689 --> 35:50.448
- Am I making myself clear?
- Yes.

35:54.034 --> 35:57.000
- I hate losing.
- Yeah, me too.

36:33.655 --> 36:35.137
So, what happened?
L or W?

36:35.275 --> 36:36.448
We lost.

36:36.586 --> 36:39.206
- Okay, so are we doing this?
- Yeah.

37:30.931 --> 37:34.620
Finally.
I was worried about you.

37:36.068 --> 37:37.827
Ah.

37:39.586 --> 37:40.758
You and Tracy lose?

37:40.896 --> 37:43.000
Yeah, they hauled
our client off in cuffs.

37:50.000 --> 37:51.827
I'm glad you came over.

37:52.862 --> 37:54.241
You alright?

37:57.517 --> 38:00.689
- Charles Theodore Riggs.
- I'm alright.

38:02.172 --> 38:04.275
You are far from alright.

38:06.724 --> 38:08.448
I hate them all.

38:09.965 --> 38:12.689
Every last one of them cops
is a piece of shit.

38:21.620 --> 38:24.137
You should have seen
the way they looked at me.

38:25.413 --> 38:27.517
Like I was garbage.

38:31.517 --> 38:35.068
Our clients get pulled up
on all the time by the cops.

38:35.965 --> 38:41.241
Stopped, frisked, searched
on the way to work.

38:41.379 --> 38:43.413
Kid sitting
on the curb handcuffed

38:43.551 --> 38:45.103
because he was wearing
a hoodie on the way

38:45.241 --> 38:48.344
to the bodega to get some milk
for his mom.

38:48.586 --> 38:49.862
We see it every day.

38:50.379 --> 38:53.551
Which I don't know
how I could possibly think

38:53.724 --> 38:56.000
that it wouldn't happen
to me now.

38:57.689 --> 39:02.689
You know, if I paid my taxes,
if I got a law degree.

39:03.137 --> 39:04.689
If I wore a suit.

39:07.724 --> 39:12.344
Somehow, stupidly,
I got comfortable.

39:13.827 --> 39:20.000
Thought I was inoculated
and boom, they got me.

39:25.482 --> 39:27.517
No escaping it either.

39:27.655 --> 39:31.206
If you're a black man,
it's only a matter of time

39:31.344 --> 39:36.241
before the police...
emasculate you.

39:40.758 --> 39:44.965
You know, I thought I was...
that I had broken free.

39:47.034 --> 39:51.206
I thought
when they looked at me,

39:53.413 --> 39:55.965
they could see m...

39:58.000 --> 39:59.689
could see me.

40:00.724 --> 40:04.344
Not just another nigga.

40:07.275 --> 40:09.172
Charlie.

40:13.793 --> 40:15.413
I see you.

40:34.724 --> 40:36.137
Next time, on "In Contempt"...

40:36.275 --> 40:37.620
Still coming
to the wedding shower, right?

40:37.758 --> 40:39.206
Of course.
I'm bringing Charlie.

40:39.344 --> 40:40.965
- Charlie from the office?
- Yeah, we're friends.

40:41.103 --> 40:42.827
What's up with you
not opening your mail?

40:43.000 --> 40:44.551
Monthly bills.

40:44.689 --> 40:46.448
To maintain my self-esteem,
I open ones I can't pay last.

40:46.586 --> 40:49.137
Ah, live like a superstar
on a reality star's budget.

40:49.275 --> 40:50.689
I'm cheating on her with you.

40:50.827 --> 40:52.413
Well, if you're so worried
about it, stop cheating.

40:52.655 --> 40:55.275
Just cause I'm new does not mean
you can take advantage of me.

40:55.413 --> 40:57.379
Don't mistake my generosity
for weakness.

40:57.551 --> 40:59.827
What's the one thing Bennett
would save in a fire?

40:59.965 --> 41:02.241
- His manuscripts.
- Gwen got it.

41:02.620 --> 41:06.620
You are the queen
of bad choices.
